## Workbook Sections

---

### 1. Overview KPIs
**Value:** Single-glance health check. Answers "how much are we spending, how fast, and how efficiently?"

| Metric | What It Tells You |
|---|---|
| Total Billed Cost ($) | Cumulative spend across all models and accounts |
| Daily Avg Cost ($) | Burn rate — is spending steady or spiking? |
| Projected Monthly ($) | Budget planning — will we blow the budget? |
| Total Tokens (K) | Consumption volume — are we using more than expected? |
| Requests | Interaction count from diagnostic logs |
| Avg Tokens/Req | Efficiency — are prompts/responses bloated? |
| Models | How many distinct models are incurring cost |

---

### 2. Cost per Model

#### Cost by Model Table
**Value:** Identifies the most expensive models and whether cost is driven by input (prompts) or output (completions). Answers "which model is eating my budget and why?"

Shows input/output/total cost per model with percentage split and pricing unit.

#### Cost Share Pie Chart
**Value:** Instant visual of cost concentration. Answers "is one model dominating spend?" — a single model >80% means vendor lock-in risk or optimization opportunity.

---

### 3. Token Usage per Model

#### Tokens by Model Table
**Value:** Reveals token economics. Token unit costs. The Input % column shows prompt-heaviness — high input % with low output may mean retrieval prompts are too long.

#### Input vs Output Bar Chart
**Value:** Visual comparison of token direction per model. Answers "are my prompts too verbose relative to completions?" — unbalanced ratios suggest prompt engineering improvements.

---

### 4. Foundry Account → Project Drill-Down

#### Foundry Account Summary (Clickable Grid)
**Value:** The command center for multi-account visibility. Answers "how is cost distributed across my Foundry accounts?" All 3 accounts appear with totals. **Click a row** to drill into that account's projects.

| Column | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Foundry Account | Account name (Costrelatedusecases, fondryprojects, foudry-orga) |
| Total Cost ($) | Aggregate spend for the account |
| Tokens (K) | Total consumed tokens |
| Models Used | Distinct model count |
| Projects | Number of projects within the account |

#### Cost Share Pie (by Account)
**Value:** Proportional view across accounts. Answers "which account is the biggest spender?" — useful for chargeback and team-level budgeting.

#### Projects Table (Conditional — appears on row click)
**Value:** Per-project breakdown within the selected account. Answers "which project inside this account is driving cost?" Shows cost, tokens, input/output split, and model count per project.

#### Cost by Project & Model (Bar Chart)
**Value:** Stacked model cost per project. Answers "within this account, which project-model combinations are most expensive?" — pinpoints the exact workload to optimize.

#### Tokens (K) by Project & Model (Bar Chart)
**Value:** Token consumption per project split by model. Answers "is one project consuming disproportionate tokens?" — helps identify inefficient prompt patterns in specific workloads.

#### Model Breakdown per Project (Table)
**Value:** The most granular view — project × model cost and tokens. Answers "if I switch this project's model, how much would I save?" — supports model migration decisions.

---

### 5. Interaction Analytics

#### Interaction Profile Table
**Value:** The operational baseline. Answers "what does a typical interaction look like?" — avg tokens/req feeds capacity planning, cost/req drives unit economics, and P95 latency sets SLA expectations.

#### Interaction Profile per Model (Table)
**Value:** Per-model breakdown showing each model's interactions, avg tokens/req, prompt/completion split, input ratio, daily request rate, latency, and total cost. Answers "how does gpt-4o behave differently than gpt-4.1?" — the Input Ratio column directly feeds the forecast simulator.

#### Interactions Over Time (Time Chart)
**Value:** Traffic pattern visualization. Answers "when do users hit the system?" — identifies peak hours for autoscaling decisions and off-peak windows for batch processing.

#### Latency Distribution (Pie Chart)
**Value:** SLA compliance at a glance. Answers "what % of requests meet our latency target?" — if >10% are in the 3-10s bucket, users are experiencing degraded UX.

#### Request Reliability Table
**Value:** Operational health per operation. Answers "are we getting throttled? Are there errors?" — 429s mean quota issues, non-200/429 errors mean bugs or service degradation.

#### Latency Over Time (Avg vs P95)
**Value:** Latency trend analysis. Answers "is latency getting worse?" — a widening gap between avg and P95 means tail latency issues, possibly from large prompts or model congestion.

---

### 6. Interactions by Project

#### Interactions by Project Table
**Value:** Per-project operational metrics. Answers "which project has reliability problems?" — surfaces per-project throttle rates and error counts so you know where to add retry logic or request quota increases.

#### Interactions Over Time by Project (Time Chart)
**Value:** Traffic split by project. Answers "which project drives peak load?" — for capacity planning and cost attribution.

#### Request Share by Project (Pie Chart)
**Value:** Proportional request volume. Answers "which project is the heaviest user of the API?" — useful for chargeback and quota allocation decisions.

---

### 7. Native Metrics by Project

#### Tokens by Project Table (AzureMetrics)
**Value:** Platform-reported token counts (not billing-derived). Answers "do the tokens reported by Azure metrics match what we're billed for?" — discrepancies reveal ingestion gaps or metering anomalies. Breaks down by ProcessedPromptTokens, GeneratedTokens, and TokenTransaction.

#### Token Trend by Project (Time Chart)
**Value:** Real-time token consumption from platform metrics. Answers "is a project's token usage trending up right now?" — faster signal than cost data (which has billing lag).

#### Requests by Project Table (AzureMetrics)
**Value:** Platform-counted requests per project. Answers "how many API calls is each project making?" — cross-reference with diagnostic logs to validate completeness.

#### Request Trend by Project (Time Chart)
**Value:** Request volume over time from platform metrics. Answers "is request volume growing?" — early warning for scaling needs before cost spikes appear.

---

### 8. Cost & Token Trends

#### Granularity Switcher (Daily/Monthly)
**Value:** Toggle between daily granularity (spot anomalies, day-level spikes) and monthly aggregation (executive reporting, budget tracking). The default is Monthly. Controls all charts and tables in this section.

#### Cost Trend by Model (Bar Chart)
**Value:** Stacked cost trend by model. Answers "did something change yesterday?" (Daily) or "how is spend evolving month-over-month?" (Monthly).

#### Token Trend by Model (Bar Chart)
**Value:** Stacked token consumption trend by model. Answers "is token usage growing, stable, or seasonal?" — consolidates the former daily token chart from Section 3.

#### Cost by Model Table
**Value:** Period-level cost journal per model. Reveals seasonal patterns, new model adoption, and retirement candidates.

#### Cost Growth Table (Period-over-Period %)
**Value:** Growth rate tracking. A positive growth % three periods running means budget escalation; negative growth after optimization confirms ROI.

---

### 9. Cost Forecast Simulator

#### Model Selector (Pills)
**Value:** Pick which model to forecast for. The input/output token ratio and avg tokens/interaction are computed from that model's actual historical data, not an aggregate.

#### Selected Model Baseline
**Value:** Shows the selected model's specific metrics: total interactions, avg tokens/interaction, prompt/completion breakdown, input ratio, and daily interaction rate. This is the data feeding the projections below.

#### Scenario Parameters
**Value:** Configurable user counts and interactions-per-user for Light/Medium/Heavy scenarios. Adjust to model your expected growth.

#### Scenario Cost Projection Table
**Value:** The money table. Combines model-specific avg tokens and input ratio with published pricing to project monthly and annual costs per scenario. Answers "if we grow to 15K heavy users on gpt-4o, what's the annual bill?"

#### Monthly Cost by Scenario (Bar Chart)
**Value:** Visual comparison of cost across scenarios. Instantly shows the cost delta between growth levels.

#### Monthly Token Volume by Scenario (Bar Chart)
**Value:** Token consumption projection. Answers "how many millions of tokens will each scenario consume?" — useful for quota planning.

